# {{projectName}}

A **Cypress + JavaScript** automation framework for **web** testing, with a **Page Object Model** structure and **{{reporter}}** reporting. Generated by QA Prism.

## Prerequisites
- Node.js 18+ (`node -v`)

## Setup
```bash
npm install
```

## Running tests
```bash
npm run cy:open   # interactive runner (pick specs, watch them run)
npm run cy:run    # headless run (CI mode)
npm test          # alias for cy:run
```

## Reports (mochawesome)
```bash
npm run cy:run
npm run report:merge
npm run report:generate   # HTML report in cypress/reports/html
```

## Structure
```
cypress/
├── e2e/        Specs (*.cy.js)
├── pages/      Page objects (POM) — BasePage + examples
├── support/    Global hooks + custom commands
└── fixtures/   Static test data
cypress.config.js
```

## Conventions
- Page objects only — no raw selectors in specs.
- Prefer `data-testid` and `cy.contains` over brittle CSS chains.
- Reusable steps become custom commands in `support/commands.js`.
- Keep static data in `fixtures/`.

